(EXHALES)

85
00:06:27,420 --> 00:06:28,722
[ISUZU, THINKING]
IT'S REALLY NICE FOR EVERYONE

86
00:06:28,822 --> 00:06:30,891
TO SAY ALL THAT STUFF
ABOUT ME...

87
00:06:30,991 --> 00:06:34,528
MUSIC HAS ALWAYS BEEN SUCH A
BIG PART OF MY LIFE, BUT...

88
00:06:35,529 --> 00:06:37,864
I MEAN, I'M GLAD NO ONE
EVER SAID I WAS BAD,

89
00:06:37,964 --> 00:06:40,033
BUT NO ONE'S GONE
SO FAR OUT OF THEIR WAY

90
00:06:40,133 --> 00:06:43,236
TO GIVE ME A COMPLIMENT, EITHER.

91
00:06:43,336 --> 00:06:47,440
SURE, I MEAN I HAVE WHAT IT
TAKES TO BECOME A PRO LIKE DAD,

92
00:06:47,541 --> 00:06:49,275
BUT IT WOULDN'T HURT
IF I PLAYED FOR FUN

93
00:06:49,375 --> 00:06:51,778
FROM TIME TO TIME, WOULD IT?

94
00:06:58,619 --> 00:07:01,688
IT SEEMED LIKE THEY
ALL ENJOYED THE SHOW!

95
00:07:01,788 --> 00:07:03,123
[TOYA]
WOW, SOMEBODY LOOKS LIKE

96
00:07:03,223 --> 00:07:04,257
THEY'VE BEEN UP TO NO GOOD, HMM?

97
00:07:04,357 --> 00:07:05,158
[ISUZU]
EHHHH!

98
00:07:05,258 --> 00:07:06,159
[TOYA]
EHEHEHEH!

99
00:07:06,259 --> 00:07:07,393
(GASP) WAIT WHAT?!

100
00:07:07,493 --> 00:07:08,662
AM I REALLY STILL SMILING?!

101
00:07:08,762 --> 00:07:10,363
[TOYA]
IT'S ALL OVER YOUR FACE!

102
00:07:10,463 --> 00:07:12,165
YOU MUST'VE REALLY
ENJOYED YOURSELF.

103
00:07:12,265 --> 00:07:13,333
YOU SOUNDED REALLY GOOD.

104
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:16,036
MMMM... THANKS...

105
00:07:16,136 --> 00:07:17,771
HMFPH! IT WAS GREAT!

106
00:07:17,871 --> 00:07:19,773
AND I NEVER THOUGHT
IN MY WILDEST DREAMS

107
00:07:19,873 --> 00:07:22,509
I'D GET TO GO UP ON STAGE
AND LAY DOWN SOME BEATS!

108
00:07:22,609 --> 00:07:24,711
YOU WERE REALLY
GOOD AT IT!

109
00:07:24,811 --> 00:07:26,046
WHATEVER!

110
00:07:26,146 --> 00:07:27,280
SERIOUSLY,

111
00:07:27,380 --> 00:07:29,049
THE BARD CLASS
IS AMAZING TO ME!

112
00:07:29,149 --> 00:07:32,519
I MEAN ABOUT IT, ALL I HAD
TO DO IS BE IN YOUR AURA

113
00:07:32,619 --> 00:07:33,720
AND RIGHT THEN AND THERE

114
00:07:33,820 --> 00:07:35,556
I SUDDENLY KNEW
HOW TO PLAY THE DRUMS.

115
00:07:35,656 --> 00:07:37,457
WELL, HERE'S THE THING.

116
00:07:37,558 --> 00:07:39,259
IT WON'T WORK IF YOU
DON'T ALREADY HAVE

117
00:07:39,359 --> 00:07:40,627
SOME KIND OF TALENT.

118
00:07:40,727 --> 00:07:43,764
AND IF YOU DON'T BELIEVE ME,
JUST ASK RUDY.

119
00:07:43,864 --> 00:07:44,798
BO‐BA‐PFFT!

120
00:07:44,898 --> 00:07:47,033
CHECK IT OUT!
I'M GETTING BETTER, RIGHT!

121
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:49,936
[RUDY] WHADDYA THINK?!
GETTIN' FUNKY NOW!

122
00:07:50,036 --> 00:07:51,705
[RUDY] AHHH! OH GOD!
(TOYA LAUGHS)

123
00:07:51,805 --> 00:07:54,007
I'M SORRY, SOMEBODY HELP ME!
[TOYA] OH WELL, NICE TRY RUDY.

124
00:07:54,107 --> 00:07:56,309
SO I... I SUPPOSE

125
00:07:56,409 --> 00:07:57,544
THAT MEANS YOU MUST HAVE

126
00:07:57,644 --> 00:07:59,179
A REALLY GOOD EAR
FOR MUSIC, HUH, ISUZU?

127
00:07:59,279 --> 00:08:00,547
UUUH NO, NOT NECESSARILY!

128
00:08:00,647 --> 00:08:02,549
IT'S JUST THAT I'VE BEEN
DOING THIS SORTA THING

129
00:08:02,649 --> 00:08:03,884
EVER SINCE I WAS A KID.

130
00:08:03,984 --> 00:08:05,752
[TOYA] I GET IT...
[ISUZU] UH?

131
00:08:05,852 --> 00:08:07,521
[TOYA]
I PLAYED SOCCER. A LOT.

132
00:08:07,621 --> 00:08:09,890
I PRACTICED ALL THE TIME.

133
00:08:09,990 --> 00:08:12,225
BUT THERE WAS NO WAY I WAS EVER
GONNA BE BETTER THAN THE GUYS

134
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:13,994
WHO JUST HAD THE KNACK FOR IT.

135
00:08:14,094 --> 00:08:18,599
YOU CAN TELL WHEN SOMEONE'S A
NATURAL, EVEN WHEN HE'S A KID.

136
00:08:19,566 --> 00:08:21,001
BUT YOU KNOW,

137
00:08:21,101 --> 00:08:24,470
I STILL HAD FUN PLAYING EVEN
THOUGH I WASN'T ALL THAT GOOD.

138
00:08:24,571 --> 00:08:25,806
JUST LIKE YOU'RE
STILL HAVING FUN

139
00:08:25,906 --> 00:08:27,307
PLAYING YOUR MUSIC, AREN'T YOU?

140
00:08:27,407 --> 00:08:31,311
UUUH...? MM‐HM.

141
00:08:31,411 --> 00:08:32,813
OF COURSE YOU ARE.

142
00:08:32,913 --> 00:08:33,914
MM‐HM.

143
00:08:34,014 --> 00:08:35,749
SO IF YOU GET A CHANCE
TO PLAY OUT THERE,

144
00:08:35,849 --> 00:08:37,017
WHAT'S THE BIG PROBLEM?

145
00:08:37,117 --> 00:08:38,685
OH...

146
00:08:40,453 --> 00:08:41,888
(ISUZU EXHALES)

147
00:08:44,290 --> 00:08:45,859
I WAS JUST THINKING...

148
00:08:45,959 --> 00:08:48,461
REMEMBER WHAT IT WAS LIKE AFTER
WE GOT SAVED FROM HAMELIN?

149
00:08:48,562 --> 00:08:50,897
[TOYA] HUH?

150
00:08:50,997 --> 00:08:53,166
[ISUZU] I'D BEEN WITH
CRESCENT MOON FOR QUITE A WHILE.

151
00:08:54,935 --> 00:08:57,270
AND THEN, YOU AND ME AND MINORI
ALL JOINED LOG HORIZON

152
00:08:57,370 --> 00:08:59,239
AROUND THE SAME TIME.

153
00:09:00,173 --> 00:09:01,775
BUT, YOU KNOW WHAT?

154
00:09:01,875 --> 00:09:03,409
I SUDDENLY HAD MY FREEDOM,

155
00:09:03,510 --> 00:09:07,013
AND I REALLY DIDN'T KNOW WHAT
I WAS GONNA DO WITH MYSELF.

156
00:09:09,850 --> 00:09:13,153
IT WASN'T LONG AFTER THAT,
I FOUND THIS LUTE.

157
00:09:13,253 --> 00:09:14,454
IT WAS JUST SITTING THERE.

158
00:09:14,555 --> 00:09:16,790
IT WAS ENGRAVED WITH A
MOTHER‐OF‐PEARL DESIGN

159
00:09:16,890 --> 00:09:19,259
THAT FOR SOME REASON,
REMINDED ME OF A DOLPHIN.

160
00:09:19,359 --> 00:09:20,894
IT WAS BEAUTIFUL!

161
00:09:20,994 --> 00:09:23,163
IT TURNS OUT THAT MARIELLE
MADE IT A LONG TIME AGO,

162
00:09:23,263 --> 00:09:26,299
SO I ASKED IF SHE WOULDN'T
MIND GIVING IT TO ME.

163
00:09:29,135 --> 00:09:31,672
IT MODIFIED IT
A COUPLE TIMES MYSELF...

164
00:09:31,772 --> 00:09:33,306
IT'S LIKE MY BABY...

165
00:09:33,406 --> 00:09:36,142
MY ONE AND ONLY,
MY FLYING DOLPHIN.

166
00:09:36,242 --> 00:09:39,580
THIS INSTRUMENT OF MINE,
IT'S ALL I REALLY NEED.

167
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:43,183
IT MOTIVATES ME TO KEEP PLAYING.

168
00:09:43,283 --> 00:09:47,087
AND PLAYING, IN TIMES LIKE
THESE, IS A REAL BLESSING.

169
00:09:47,187 --> 00:09:48,589
MPH.

170
00:09:51,124 --> 00:09:53,326
[MINORI] TOYA! ISUZU!
[BOTH] HUH?

171
00:09:54,961 --> 00:09:56,296
HUH? HEY!

172
00:09:56,396 --> 00:09:57,731
BACK ALREADY?

173
00:09:57,831 --> 00:10:00,601
[MINORI] SO UH... SHIROE NEEDS
TO TELL US SOMETHING?

174
00:10:00,701 --> 00:10:03,003
NOT SURE WHAT ABOUT,
BUT HE SAID IT'S IMPORTANT.

175
00:10:03,103 --> 00:10:04,705
[BOTH]
HUH?

176
00:10:12,713 --> 00:10:14,347
[TOYA]
WE'RE GOING ON A QUEST?!

177
00:10:14,447 --> 00:10:15,916
REALLY? THAT'S AWESOME!

178
00:10:16,016 --> 00:10:18,384
THOSE ARE THE REDSTONE MOUNTAINS
AROUND NAGANO, AREN'T THEY?!

179
00:10:18,484 --> 00:10:21,888
THERE'RE GONNA BE ALL KINDS OF
MOUNTAINS, RIVERS, AND FORESTS!

180
00:10:21,988 --> 00:10:24,691
ON TOP OF THAT, WE'RE GONNA
MEET A WHOLE BUNCHA NEW PEOPLE!

181
00:10:24,791 --> 00:10:27,393
[MINORI] TOYA! YOU NEED TO
FOCUS ON PACKING.

182
00:10:27,493 --> 00:10:28,795
AND DON'T FORGET YOUR UNDERWEAR!

183
00:10:28,895 --> 00:10:31,431
COME ON! I CAN ONLY JAM
SO MUCH STUFF INTO MY BAG.

184
00:10:31,532 --> 00:10:33,266
IF WE'RE LUCKY WHILE
WE'RE OUT THERE,

185
00:10:33,366 --> 00:10:34,635
MAYBE I'LL GET THE MAGIC BAG.

186
00:10:34,735 --> 00:10:36,570
FORTUNATELY, YOU HAVE
A WELL‐SEASONED

187
00:10:36,670 --> 00:10:39,640
TRAVELER EXTRAORDINAIRE
IN RUNDELLHAUS KODE!

188
00:10:39,740 --> 00:10:41,141
OH YEAH, THAT'S RIGHT!

189
00:10:41,241 --> 00:10:43,009
YOU'VE ALREADY DONE A LOT OF
TRAVELING HAVEN'T YOU RUDY?!

190
00:10:43,109 --> 00:10:46,112
YES! WHILE IT WAS TRUE
I TRAVELED WITH AN ADVENTURER

191
00:10:46,212 --> 00:10:49,716
TO BOGPORT, I MADE THE REST
OF THE JOURNEY A' SOLO.

192
00:10:49,816 --> 00:10:52,385
I HAVE A WEALTH OF EXPERIENCE!

193
00:10:52,485 --> 00:10:53,453
HUH?

194
00:10:53,554 --> 00:10:54,487
AAAUUGHHHHH!!!

195
00:10:54,588 --> 00:10:56,456
HUH? RUDY, YOU OKAY?

196
00:10:56,557 --> 00:10:58,625
WHERE IN GOD'S NAME
IS MY HAIRBRUSH!

197
00:10:58,725 --> 00:11:00,326
I CAN'T MAINTAIN MY
INCREDIBLENESS

198
00:11:00,426 --> 00:11:01,695
WITHOUT MY DIVINE COIFFURE!

199
00:11:01,795 --> 00:11:04,030
MY ELEGANT STRANDS WILL
BE BUT A NEST OF RATS!

200
00:11:04,130 --> 00:11:06,132
[RUDY] BY THE GODS,
WHY HAVE I BEEN BROUGHT

201
00:11:06,232 --> 00:11:08,502
THIS VILE PUNISHMENT!
[ISUZU] WHOA, EASY. FOUND IT.

202
00:11:08,602 --> 00:11:10,504
[RUDY] OOOH! UH?
[ISUZU] HERE. UH?

203
00:11:10,604 --> 00:11:11,805
AAAH! MISS ISUZU!

204
00:11:11,905 --> 00:11:14,474
YOU'VE SINGLE‐HANDEDLY
SAVED MY MANLINESS!

205
00:11:14,575 --> 00:11:15,876
[ISUZU] UHAH! OKAY,

206
00:11:15,976 --> 00:11:17,711
WELL USE YOUR MANLINESS
TO PICK ALL THIS CRAP UP.

207
00:11:17,811 --> 00:11:19,946
(GIGGLES)

208
00:11:20,046 --> 00:11:21,982
ARE YOU PIPSQUEAKS
READY TO GET AFTER IT?

209
00:11:22,082 --> 00:11:23,884
[TOYA]
YOU KNOW IT, MASTER NAOTSUGU!

210
00:11:23,984 --> 00:11:26,252
[NAOTSUGU] MAKE SURE YOU GET
A FEW BARRELS OF AGUA

211
00:11:26,352 --> 00:11:27,554
LOADED UP ON THE WAGON.

212
00:11:27,654 --> 00:11:28,689
[TOYA]
WE GOT IT COVERED!

213
00:11:28,789 --> 00:11:30,924
GOOD JOB.

214
00:11:31,424 --> 00:11:33,193
HUH? WHAAA?!

215
00:11:33,293 --> 00:11:35,361
[TETORA] HOW'S EVERYBODY DOIN'?!
ARE YOU OKAY?!

216
00:11:35,461 --> 00:11:37,964
HEY! GET YOUR SCRAWNY
BUTT OUTTA MY SHIRT!

217
00:11:38,064 --> 00:11:39,365
[NAOTSUGU] I'M NOT KIDDIN'!

218
00:11:39,465 --> 00:11:41,067
[TETORA] IF YA WANT ANY
ADVICE ON THE BESTEST AND

219
00:11:41,167 --> 00:11:44,204
SAFEST WAYS TO TRAVEL,
